§o§0     ＧＴＡＩＶｉｓｂｅｓｔ§r
#- §lThe Death of Dan§r

§0The sky was bleak, grey and oppressive, the streets barren and cold in the cloud-filtered light. The announcement from general Thoths of the Augustan Armed Forces was coming through all the radios of Mt. Augusta and beyond, his voice§r
#- grainy and tense. Families huddled around their living rooms or kitchens, listening intently, fathers clutching their wives and children.

§0"§r§o§0Lord Mayor ProgrammerDan passed away this morning...§r§0"§r

§0The air was as heavy as lead. Many§r
#- didn't believe the news, some were angry, some cried, some simply stayed silent. The voice on the radio went on, following the script.

§0"§r§o§0...Pronounced§r§o§0 dead at the scene...§r§0". Slowly, the disbelievers despaired, and broke into tears at the§r
#- realisation.

§0Doors began to open, and out came citizens, stumbling onto the cold grey streets, crying, yelling, lamenting ProgrammerDan. Some found their solace sitting upon the curb, comforting each other silently. Others wandered the streets,§r
#- crying with their heads turned to the sky. "§o§0What will we do now? How could this happen?§r§0". Over the rooftops and out towards central Augusta, the only sound that could be heard was distant crying and lamenting. In that moment, the city collectively §r
#- broke down.

§0A few hundred meters East, the citizens of New Detroit, capital of the Gensokyojin Federation, were just now beginning to wake. News of the disaster in Augusta was starting to filter in, but in the form of rumours and unverified §r
#- exaggerations. Most of the citizenry, kept in the dark, ignored those unsubstantiated stories from over the wall. In the Palace of Earthly Spirits, queen Screename was eating breakfast when she heard the radio broadcast. The teacup she was holding slipped
#- from her fingers and shattered against the marble floor, sending bits of clay and tea dancing across the palace. Immediately images burned in her mind of instability, the riots, the military coup, war on the horizon. Her face found her way to her hands,
#- and she clutched herself in despair as her servants rushed into the room.

§0Up North, the first merchantmen were opening their stalls in the §r§o§0Bazaar al-Kabir§r§0 underneath the capital city of Istanbul. The radios they had, perched upon ledges from §r
#- within their stalls, were broadcasting the ISIS state radio station. Among the dusty early-morning Bazaar atmosphere, filled with the sounds of opening stalls, Arabic conversation and distant music, the regular programming of the radio was interrupted for
#- an important piece of news from Mt. Augusta. Gradually, as the Arabic commentator translated the speech from general Thoths, the Bazaar fell silent, and the Jellabah'd men walked slowly out into the open plaza, facing South towards Augusta, some softly
#- muttering words of prayer.

§0"§r§o§0Allahu akbar, allahu akbar... Ya rabi, ya bismillah§r§0". The radio commentator's voice broke for a moment before continuing on:§r

§0"§r§o§0رئيس بلدية مبرمج مي§r§0"§r

§0"ProgrammerDan is dead."§r
#- Miles away, in the §o§0Villa al-Sultan§r§0 just North of Istanbul, Sultan GTAIVisbest shot up straight in his bed, and staying absolutely still, clenched his eyes shut and listened to the radio repeat what had just been said. He swore softly, swung his§r
#- trembling legs out from under the covers, and staggered to his window, watching the first plumes of smoke rise from the distant South.

§0"§r§o§0May Allah have mercy upon us all.§r§0"§r
#- 